  "title": "AV & Workplace Technology Project Manager",
  "description": "<p>Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Information Technology, Project Management, or related field.</p><p>• 8+ years of progressive experience in managing large-scale, complex projects,with a significant focus on commercial real estate/workplace projects and/or AV/IT deployments.</p><p>• Proven track record in delivering projects involving:</p><p>o Raceway and cable management systems</p><p>o Raised floor and hub room design</p><p>o Power sizing and electrical coordination</p><p>o Network and Wi-Fi infrastructure</p><p>o AV systems integration (Crestron, Shure, Biamp, Jabra and  ennheiser)</p><p>o Collaboration platforms (Microsoft Teams Rooms)</p><p>o LED display solutions</p><p>o Access control and security systems</p><p>• In-depth knowledge of current and emerging AV technologies (e.g., video conferencing platforms like Zoom/Teams, control systems like Crestron/Extron).</p><p>• Excellent interpersonal, negotiation, and communication skills (written and verbal) to effectively manage diverse stakeholder groups.</p><p>• Proficiency in budget management and project scheduling tools.</p>",
